<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I think it would be nice to have a validation method for ini-files.</p>

<p>The method would probably check if each line is either a comment or a config directive of type "key = value" using valid syntax (are there other things than comments and directives that could/should be in a ini-file?), and throw exceptions when encountering something else.</p>

<p>This way we could inform the user if they have accidentally created an invalid ini-file.</p>

